--------------------------------------------------\
RISKS AND MITIGATIONS\
--------------------------------------------------\
Risk: Property path design is wrong\
- Mitigation: finalize path contract before broad tool implementation.\
- Mitigation: build introspection tools first and verify round-trip behavior.\
Risk: Value serialization becomes inconsistent\
- Mitigation: centralize serialization in shared JSX helpers and golden tests.\
Risk: Names/indexes are unstable\
- Mitigation: always return IDs and canonical handles in responses.\
Risk: AE-version-specific behavior causes breakage\
- Mitigation: capability checks and VERSION_UNSUPPORTED errors.\
Risk: Over-engineering early\
- Mitigation: only modularize/generate after core abstractions are proven.\
Risk: Bridge transport redesign wastes time\
- Mitigation: keep current transport unless real concurrency failures appear.\
--------------------------------------------------\
LLM-SPECIFIC IMPLEMENTATION RULES\
--------------------------------------------------\
The AI coding LLM implementing this plan should follow these behavioral rules:\
- Prefer read-first design.\
- Every mutating tool should have a corresponding inspection/verification path.\
- Return both stable machine handles and human-readable names.\
- Prefer strict schemas and enums over free-form strings.\
- Include follow-up-ready handles in responses.\
- Preserve raw AE details alongside normalized data when helpful.\
- Mark operations conceptually as safe/destructive/version-dependent.\
- Avoid introducing too many convenience tools before the primitives are solid.\
--------------------------------------------------\
SUGGESTED FILE-LEVEL EXECUTION OUTLINE\
--------------------------------------------------\
This is a suggested implementation order at the codebase level.\
1. Add contract/type files for:\
- envelopes\
- errors\
- handles\
- property paths\
- serialized values\
2. Extract bridge logic from src/index.ts into dedicated bridge modules.\
3. Introduce shared schema modules for common identifiers.\
4. Refactor src/scripts/mcp-bridge-auto.jsx to add shared helper functions before adding many new commands.\
5. Implement read-only introspection tools first.\
6. Add mutation tools that reuse the same identifiers/serializers.\
7. After patterns stabilize, split monolithic tool registration into modular registries.\
8. Add docs and tests once the first contract-complete vertical slice is working.\
